Day 15 – Caching with Redis
1️⃣ What is Caching?

Caching = Store frequently accessed data in fast memory (Redis) instead of DB.

Without Cache:
App → DB (slow)

With Cache:
App → Redis (fast) → DB only if cache miss


Speed:

DB query → 20–200 ms

Redis → 1–5 ms

